Ontology Specification Draft

Abstract

OWL Classes

There are currently eight classes in the ontology, each of which represents an entry in the DRS as well a two object properties to link sensors and platforms.
OWL Classes

Concept Schemes

The named individuals of each class are also represented as concepts in SKOS concept schemes: data type, ecv, frequency, institutes, platforms, processing levels, products, and sensors. The use of a concept scheme allows easy navigation up and down the tree as well as providing relationships to concepts from other DRS. As well as relationships between sensors and platforms, each ECV concept is related to one or more data type concepts.

SKOS Navigation Down the Concept Scheme
SKOS Navigation Up the Concept Scheme

Collections

The named individuals of each class are also represented as members in SKOS collections: data type, ecv, frequency, institutes, platforms, processing levels, products, and sensors. As well as relationships between sensors and platforms, each ECV concept is related to one or more data type concepts.

<p>The CCI concept schemes are used to define concepts within an element of a Directory Reference Scheme. There are currently eight concept schemes defined: <a href=../dataType>data type</a>, <a href=..//ecv>ecv</a>, <a href=../scheme/cci/freq>frequency</a>, <a href=../org>institutes</a>, <a href=../platform>platforms</a>, <a href=../procLev>processing levels</a>, <a href=../product>products</a>, and <a href=../sensor>sensors</a>. The use of a concept scheme allows easy navigation up and down the tree.</p><h5>SKOS Navigation Down the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeDown.svg /><h5>SKOS Navigation Up the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeUp.svg /><p>As well as being concepts the the concepts are also named individuals of the <a href=../../../ontology/cci>CCI Ontology</a> classes.<h5>OWL Classes</h5><img src=classes.svg /><p></p>

Instituteni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: http://vocab.ceda.ac.uk/scheme/cci/org

This concept scheme represents the organisations in the CCI project
Organisations (institutions) that are involved in production of data for the ESA Climate Change Initiative (CCI).
<p>The CCI concept schemes are used to define concepts within an element of a Directory Reference Scheme. There are currently eight concept schemes defined: <a href=../dataType>data type</a>, <a href=..//ecv>ecv</a>, <a href=../scheme/cci/freq>frequency</a>, <a href=../org>institutes</a>, <a href=../platform>platforms</a>, <a href=../procLev>processing levels</a>, <a href=../product>products</a>, and <a href=../sensor>sensors</a>. The use of a concept scheme allows easy navigation up and down the tree.</p><h5>SKOS Navigation Down the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeDown.svg /><h5>SKOS Navigation Up the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeUp.svg /><p>As well as being concepts the the concepts are also named individuals of the <a href=../../../ontology/cci>CCI Ontology</a> classes.<h5>OWL Classes</h5><img src=classes.svg /><p></p>

Platformni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: http://vocab.ceda.ac.uk/scheme/cci/platform

This concept scheme represents the platforms used by the CCI project
The platforms that have been used in the collection of data for the ESA Climate Change Initiative (CCI).
<p>The CCI concept schemes are used to define concepts within an element of a Directory Reference Scheme. There are currently eight concept schemes defined: <a href=../dataType>data type</a>, <a href=..//ecv>ecv</a>, <a href=../scheme/cci/freq>frequency</a>, <a href=../org>institutes</a>, <a href=../platform>platforms</a>, <a href=../procLev>processing levels</a>, <a href=../product>products</a>, and <a href=../sensor>sensors</a>. The use of a concept scheme allows easy navigation up and down the tree.</p><h5>SKOS Navigation Down the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeDown.svg /><h5>SKOS Navigation Up the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeUp.svg /><p>As well as being concepts the the concepts are also named individuals of the <a href=../../../ontology/cci>CCI Ontology</a> classes.<h5>OWL Classes</h5><img src=classes.svg /><p></p>

Sensorni back to ToC or Named Individual ToC

IRI: http://vocab.ceda.ac.uk/scheme/cci/sensor

This concept scheme represents the sensors used by the CCI project
The sensors that have been used in the collection of the data for the ESA Climate Change Initiative (CCI).
<p>The CCI concept schemes are used to define concepts within an element of a Directory Reference Scheme. There are currently eight concept schemes defined: <a href=../dataType>data type</a>, <a href=..//ecv>ecv</a>, <a href=../scheme/cci/freq>frequency</a>, <a href=../org>institutes</a>, <a href=../platform>platforms</a>, <a href=../procLev>processing levels</a>, <a href=../product>products</a>, and <a href=../sensor>sensors</a>. The use of a concept scheme allows easy navigation up and down the tree.</p><h5>SKOS Navigation Down the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeDown.svg /><h5>SKOS Navigation Up the Concept Scheme</h5><img src=conceptSchemeUp.svg /><p>As well as being concepts the the concepts are also named individuals of the <a href=../../../ontology/cci>CCI Ontology</a> classes.<h5>OWL Classes</h5><img src=classes.svg /><p></p>
